\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 along the way e.g if the task is to find a nice place to sleep in the kitchen
 you could have a random thought about the content of the refrigerator when
 you are close to it, and it is the player can choose to act on this thought.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For example the humans task could be to make a salad with tuna in it.
 The cat detects this, and like the cunning creature that it is pretends
 to continue sleeping until the tuna can is open and placed on the table.
 Then it 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

accidentally pushes something over in the living roam, and hides.
 hen the human comes to deal with the mess in the living room the cat sneaks
 in to the kitchen to steal tuna.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As the point of the game is to focus on the cat-human interaction some of
 the trivial actions will be simplified so that when the actor is going
 from one place to an other the player does not have control them precisely.
 The same goes for the cooking actions.
 this is not a skill based game.
 The point is on the player decisions.
 
\end_layout

